{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17656331","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17656331"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:11:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:11:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18718"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18718","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18718"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11450"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77062"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11450","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11450"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18718"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62568"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10577"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26513"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26520"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77062","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77062"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EEjaculation is a complex physiological process involving coordinated actions of multiple organs and muscle groups under autonomic and somatic neural control.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the correct sequence of events during ejaculation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Emission without expulsion","Emission followed by expulsion","Simultaneous emission and expulsion","Expulsion followed by emission","Expulsion without emission"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct sequence is \u003Cstrong\u003Eemission followed by expulsion\u003C/strong\u003E. During emission, sympathetic nerves (T10-L2) stimulate:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EContraction of the vas deferens and epididymis to move sperm\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ESecretion from the prostate and seminal vesicles\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EClosure of the bladder neck\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis deposits reproductive fluids into the posterior urethra. The expulsion phase then follows, involving rhythmic contractions of the bulbospongiosus and other pelvic floor muscles under somatic control (S2-4) to expel semen from the urethra.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpulsion followed by emission\u003C/strong\u003E - This sequence is physiologically impossible as expulsion requires prior deposition of fluids in the urethra\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESimultaneous emission and expulsion\u003C/strong\u003E - These are distinct sequential phases that cannot occur simultaneously\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpulsion without emission\u003C/strong\u003E - Expulsion cannot occur without prior emission of fluids into the urethra\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEmission without expulsion\u003C/strong\u003E - While theoretically possible, this would not result in ejaculation\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ejaculation consists of two distinct phases: emission and expulsion.","The emission phase involves deposition of sperm and secretions into the posterior urethra via sympathetic control.","The expulsion phase involves rhythmic contractions of pelvic muscles to expel semen from the urethra via somatic control."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62568"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18718"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62568","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62568"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-05T23:28:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T23:28:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11450"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77062"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4934","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4934"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf46","name":"Reproductive System (Male)","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-21T12:54:34+10:30"},"relationships"